---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import NextSteps from '../components/NextSteps.astro';
import ConceptLink from '../components/ConceptLink.astro';
import DiagramPlate from '../components/DiagramPlate.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="The Theory"
  description="A short introduction to Ontogony and the Transductive Universe."
  kind="THEORY"
  active="OVERVIEW"
>
  <p class="kicker">The Theory</p>
  <h1 class="page-title">Ontogony</h1>
  <p class="lede">
    A theory of becoming, built from the bottom up. About what it costs for
    anything to be the kind of thing it is, and how new kinds of things come
    into being at all.
  </p>
  <DiagramPlate
    title="The Four Registers of Ontogony"
    caption="The R1-R4 register map organizes Ontogony's macro-regimes of persistence: field, biological, cognitive, and institutional."
    image="/images/diagrams/four-registers.png"
    href="/diagrams/r1-r4-strata"
  />
  <hr />

  <div class="prose">
    <p>
      Ontogony starts from a simple observation: persistence is not free. Every
      regime that holds itself together against the second law does so at a
      measurable rate of energy dissipation. That rate is constitutive of what
      the regime <em>is</em>, not incidental to it.
    </p>
    <p>
      From that single commitment, a framework follows. The general operator at
      its centre is <ConceptLink slug="transduction">transduction</ConceptLink> —
      the irreversible resolution of a metastable field through which a new regime,
      with its own vocabulary and its own conditions of failure, precipitates.
      Transduction is what happens when the universe installs a new register of
      description, and it is the structural shape that links a crystal forming,
      a cell metabolising, and a symbolic system bootstrapping its own
      grammar.
    </p>
    <p>
      The theory is being written as a long book. This site is the field guide:
      a set of short, self-contained entries that let a stranger get the shape
      of the project quickly, and a serious reader trace the threads in
      whatever order they prefer.
    </p>
  </div>

  <NextSteps
    heading="Where to start"
    concepts={['transduction']}
  />
</BaseLayout>
